The paper deals with algorithms for maintaining data depth measures, which are commonly studied in computational geometry and statistics. The use of dynamic algorithms suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms, which falls under cs.DS. The mention of half-space depth and contours suggests a connection to computational geometry, which falls under cs.CG. The paper also discusses the maintenance of rank-based and cover-based contours, which are related to machine learning and data analysis, falling under cs.SI and cs.LG. Finally, the use of logarithmic time and space complexities suggests a connection to information theory, falling under cs.IT.
